		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">yatagarasu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Also - where on the NES board should I ground any audio jack? <br /></div>
<br />
<br />I had the same problem a little while ago when i did my stereo mod. You could do it the right way, find some IC's that you know the layout for and measure a ground pin and various obvious places on the motherboard. OR you can just get tired of the whole project like i did and do it the easy way, just ground it in one of the screws that holds the metal shield .. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />

		

		</td>
